<title>USA: IMF warns investors of fraudulent schemes.</title>
<headline>IMF warns investors of fraudulent schemes.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1996-11-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>The International Monetary Fund warned investors on Monday to beware of fraudulent financial schemes that claim to have its blessing and promise high returns.</p>
<p>&quot;The IMF does not operate through other agents and it does not endorse the activities of any bank, financial institution or other public or private agency,&quot; it said in a statement.</p>
<p>An IMF spokesman said the Fund issued its warning in response to a wave of such schemes over the past six months.</p>
<p>Many appear to originate in the former Soviet Union, but other areas, including Britain, the Channel Islands, Germany and Nigeria, have also been involved. Many of the victims seem to reside in the United States.</p>
<p>The IMF issued similar warnings to investors two years ago, in response to a wave of fraudulent schemes at that time.</p>
